1
00:00:02,711 --> 00:00:04,754
[QIFREY] There are
many kinds of magic,

2
00:00:04,755 --> 00:00:07,423
but some are
of particular importance.

3
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:09,050
Four, to be precise.

4
00:00:11,386 --> 00:00:14,221
Granting control
over that nourishing force

5
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:16,223
that sustains all life...

6
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:17,685
the Sigil of Water.

7
00:00:18,936 --> 00:00:22,146
Turning stone to sand
and sand to stone,

8
00:00:22,147 --> 00:00:24,565
enabling transformation
and movement...

9
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:26,443
the Sigil of Earth.

10
00:00:27,862 --> 00:00:30,613
Making travel
to distant realms a reality,

11
00:00:30,614 --> 00:00:33,408
through which so much progress
has been achieved...

12
00:00:33,993 --> 00:00:35,911
the Sigil of Levitation.

13
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:37,454
And finally,

14
00:00:37,705 --> 00:00:40,624
no less than humanity's
very sword and shield...

15
00:00:41,876 --> 00:00:43,711
the Sigil of Flame.

16
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:48,882
Witches hold these four sigils
to be their foundation,

17
00:00:48,883 --> 00:00:50,885
the Primary Tetrad.

18
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:53,136
- [Coco gasps]
- [QIFREY] So, then...

19
00:00:53,554 --> 00:00:55,430
shall we give them a try?

20
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:59,058
[brushbuddy snores squeakily]

21
00:00:59,393 --> 00:01:01,102
[scribbling]

22
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:07,734
[Tetia groans]

23
00:01:07,735 --> 00:01:09,109
[Coco grunts softly]

24
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:10,445
[Tetia sighs]

25
00:01:11,363 --> 00:01:12,656
[Tetia sighs]

26
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:14,615
Hmm.

27
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:15,742
[Coco yelps]

28
00:01:15,743 --> 00:01:18,662
No, no, no!
What do I do now? Help!

29
00:01:19,038 --> 00:01:20,163
[Coco exclaims]

30
00:01:21,248 --> 00:01:22,374
[Coco groans]

31
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:25,083
There. Are you all right?

32
00:01:25,084 --> 00:01:27,253
[COCO]
Thank you for that, Tetia.

33
00:01:27,254 --> 00:01:29,630
[Tetia chuckles]
Thank you for your thanks!

34
00:01:29,631 --> 00:01:32,258
What were you trying to do, anyway?

35
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:34,385
Practice my levitation magic

36
00:01:34,386 --> 00:01:36,805
by drawing the Pyreball spell.

37
00:01:37,598 --> 00:01:38,932
Word of warning.

38
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:41,392
The Sigil of Fire deals
with formless phenomena

39
00:01:41,393 --> 00:01:43,853
and becomes dangerous
when out of balance,

40
00:01:43,854 --> 00:01:45,480
so be sure to take care.

41
00:01:46,023 --> 00:01:47,273
[COCO] I will.

42
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:48,734
[TETIA] Hm?

43
00:01:51,028 --> 00:01:53,905
I thought you already mastered
levitation magic

44
00:01:53,906 --> 00:01:55,031
at the Dadah Range.

45
00:01:55,032 --> 00:01:57,076
Why do you still need
to practice it?

46
00:01:57,701 --> 00:02:00,703
You were out there whoosh-whoosh
whooshing around, right?

47
00:02:00,704 --> 00:02:01,956
Whoosh-whoosh-whoosh...

48
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,248
I suppose...

49
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:07,628
But I ruined the Sylph Shoes
Agott let me borrow.

50
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:11,048
I couldn't return them
to her like that.

51
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,673
I've restored everything

52
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:15,051
but the Casting Seal
on the soles.

53
00:02:15,052 --> 00:02:17,846
The lines I draw
keep coming out wobbly.

54
00:02:18,722 --> 00:02:20,057
[QIFREY] Perhaps...

55
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:22,810
this pen isn't right for you.

56
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:25,728
I merely picked it
from my own at random.

57
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:27,730
There may be another
that better suits you,

58
00:02:27,731 --> 00:02:29,984
in terms of weight and grip.

59
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:31,568
Yes, of course.

60
00:02:31,902 --> 00:02:34,570
On reflection, I think it's time
you chose one for yourself.

61
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:35,822
[Coco gasps]

62
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:37,949
[Tetia gasps, giggles]

63
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:40,534
Next stop, magic stationer's!

64
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:41,786
Stationer's?

65
00:02:41,787 --> 00:02:44,914
Yes, they carry all manner
of magical goods.

66
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:46,457
Pens and ink and the like.

67
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,084
[COCO]
So they sell art supplies?

68
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:49,877
Magical art supplies.

69
00:02:49,878 --> 00:02:52,588
[gasps] It sounds so wonderful!

70
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:55,299
If I'm dreaming,
please don't wake me!

71
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,592
Ah, Coco?

72
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,678
[COCO] This is all
so much to take in.

73
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:00,429
I think I need to lie down.

74
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:01,807
[brushbuddy squeaks]

75
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:33,774
[wind blowing]

76
00:04:39,071 --> 00:04:40,572
♪

77
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,245
[Coco exclaims]

78
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:48,747
[QIFREY] That island
on the sandbar is Kalhn...

79
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:51,041
...Township of the Marshwoods.

80
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:53,543
It's the closest witches' town
to our atelier.

81
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:02,844
[Coco exclaims]

82
00:05:03,302 --> 00:05:05,554
- [girl laughs]
- [BOY] Wait for me!

83
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:07,807
A Casting Seal that makes
your skirt fuller!

84
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:10,308
I was afraid
the ink wasn't compatible.

85
00:05:10,309 --> 00:05:12,352
[COCO]
Look at all these witches.

86
00:05:12,353 --> 00:05:15,064
Would you care to learn
about the city's history?

87
00:05:15,065 --> 00:05:16,941
For protection from
the molewyrms

88
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:18,567
on the far bank
of the Marshwoods,

89
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:21,070
the witches built part
of the sandbar into an island

90
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:23,197
that could support a watchtower.

91
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,241
Then, as more witches
gathered here,

92
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:26,742
it became an atelier town,

93
00:05:26,743 --> 00:05:28,244
- and to this day...
- Uh, Master Qifrey?

94
00:05:28,245 --> 00:05:29,996
- She's not listening.
- [AGOTT] Excuse me.

95
00:05:29,997 --> 00:05:32,665
Thrilling as it would be
to play tour guide for Coco,

96
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:34,250
I have better things to do.

97
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:36,252
And shops I'd like to visit.

98
00:05:36,253 --> 00:05:37,920
I'm going off on my own.

99
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:39,964
We'll meet you
at the magic stationer's!

100
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:41,008
[Coco sighs]

101
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,259
[QIFREY] So,
how are things going

102
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:45,179
with you and Agott?

103
00:05:46,096 --> 00:05:47,931
[COCO] I'm not sure, but...

104
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,642
I hope we can be friends
someday.

105
00:06:02,904 --> 00:06:04,238
[Coco exclaims]

106
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:06,533
- [TETIA] Coco! Over here!
- [Coco gasps]

107
00:06:07,075 --> 00:06:08,743
Don't get left behind!

108
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,122
Wow.

109
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:14,124
[Coco chuckles softly]

110
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,793
Incredible.
It's like a dream.

111
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:18,837
Uh?

112
00:06:20,964 --> 00:06:22,341
[Coco exclaims]

113
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:29,097
[Coco gasps softly]

114
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:37,146
[TETIA] Coco!

115
00:06:37,147 --> 00:06:39,607
We're not supposed
to get separated!

116
00:06:44,654 --> 00:06:47,365
[TETIA] Kalhn's full of people,
isn't it?

117
00:06:47,366 --> 00:06:50,202
[RICHEH] Too many.
It makes me tired.

118
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,410
The magic stationer's.

119
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:54,121
It's called the Starry Sword.

120
00:06:54,122 --> 00:06:55,249
[Coco gasps softly]

121
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:57,542
[door creaks]

122
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:01,213
[birds chirping]

123
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:10,429
[Coco gasps softly]

124
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,808
[footsteps]

125
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,230
[birds chirping]

126
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:21,648
There's a tree growing through
the middle of the shop.

127
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:23,025
[MAN] My, my!

128
00:07:23,026 --> 00:07:25,527
Now this is surprising.

129
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:29,241
A witch's apprentice gawking
at a Silverwood Tree.

130
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:34,120
Are you unfamiliar
with something so elementary?

131
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:35,621
None of that.

132
00:07:35,622 --> 00:07:38,125
Coco here is still
a relatively new apprentice.

133
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:40,626
Oh! Coco, you say?

134
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:43,422
So, she's the one.

135
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:47,967
Well, now,
that clears things up!

136
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:50,677
Sorry, wee one!
Of course you wouldn't know it.

137
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:53,847
Suppose all's fair.
I didn't recognize you either.

138
00:07:53,848 --> 00:07:57,059
Seems we're even! [laughs]

139
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,853
That's Mr. Nolnoa!

140
00:07:59,354 --> 00:08:01,897
He's the owner
of the Starry Sword!

141
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,107
That I am!

142
00:08:03,108 --> 00:08:05,818
With the help
of my grandson Tartah,

143
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:08,862
I made all the components
you see in this establishment.

144
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:13,575
All the pens, all the ink,
all of it! No exceptions!

145
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:17,371
I can also extract ink
at any concentration.

146
00:08:17,372 --> 00:08:18,999
Extract it?

147
00:08:20,417 --> 00:08:21,875
[clears throat]

148
00:08:21,876 --> 00:08:24,502
Yes, why don't I show you,
Coco, wasn't it?

149
00:08:24,503 --> 00:08:25,838
Come along, now.

150
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,132
Yes, sir!

151
00:08:32,137 --> 00:08:33,430
[snipping]

152
00:08:44,358 --> 00:08:45,484
[Coco gasps softly]

153
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:53,158
[COCO] Uh?

154
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:56,119
[birds chirping]

155
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:07,214
[NOLNOA] Hmm.

156
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:19,308
- [Coco gasps softly]
- [Tetia chuckles softly]

157
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:21,435
- [brushbuddy squeals]
- It turned black!

158
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:23,229
That is called Woodcruor.

159
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:26,482
Its branches are silvery white
when alive and healthy,

160
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,735
but quickly turn black
upon their death.

161
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:31,569
In that state,
it becomes toxic,

162
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:34,408
both to humans
and to the tree itself.

163
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:35,616
And yet,

164
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,327
through a simple process
of dissolving it in water

165
00:09:38,328 --> 00:09:40,788
and then straining out
the excess...

166
00:09:41,498 --> 00:09:45,000
we have a crude Conjuring Ink,
no less than

167
00:09:45,001 --> 00:09:47,628
- the very source of all magic.
- [Coco gasps softly]

168
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:51,882
Regular ink is made
from the soot that's produced

169
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:54,592
when you burn normal wood.
But Conjuring Ink...

170
00:09:54,593 --> 00:09:55,886
that's different.

171
00:09:55,887 --> 00:09:58,055
It's made
from the tree's "cruor."

172
00:09:58,056 --> 00:10:00,015
Literally, its blood.

173
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,767
As I'm sure you can imagine,

174
00:10:01,768 --> 00:10:05,145
the Silverwood is an extremely
important tree to witches.

175
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:08,107
I should say!
Why, they're the only tree

176
00:10:08,108 --> 00:10:10,192
from which the ink
can be extracted.

177
00:10:10,193 --> 00:10:12,027
It sounds amazing!

178
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,405
- Precious, too.
- Both true!

179
00:10:14,406 --> 00:10:16,324
There's even
an old legend about it!

180
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:20,536
[NOLNOA] As the story goes,
a long time ago,

181
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:24,290
there was a Silverwood tree
that fell in love with a witch!

182
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:26,417
It offered its branches
as wands,

183
00:10:26,418 --> 00:10:29,044
- and its blood as ink.
- Wands?

184
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:31,004
Uh? [laughs]

185
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:33,132
Is that why
you're here today?

186
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,800
- To buy a wand?
- Yes!

187
00:10:34,801 --> 00:10:36,927
[Nolnoa chuckles]

188
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:39,388
[Nolnoa humming]

189
00:10:39,389 --> 00:10:40,639
Ah...

190
00:10:42,476 --> 00:10:43,810
Well, then...

191
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,438
go on and try a few out.

192
00:10:53,612 --> 00:10:55,780
You'll need this, of course.

193
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:00,493
I'm sure you
and the perfect wand

194
00:11:00,494 --> 00:11:01,994
will find each other.

195
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:03,871
[Coco gasps]

196
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:06,583
[footsteps]

197
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:08,666
[TETIA] Have any idea
what you want?

198
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:11,462
I really like lighter wands,
if you want my opinion!

199
00:11:11,463 --> 00:11:12,964
[COCO] Which should I try first?

200
00:11:16,510 --> 00:11:17,927
[Coco gasps]

201
00:11:18,553 --> 00:11:20,804
[COCO] Hold on! Come back!

202
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,265
[Tetia pants]

203
00:11:24,683 --> 00:11:26,060
Coco, wait!

204
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:28,854
- Oh! What do we do?
- [brushbuddy squeaks softly]

205
00:11:28,855 --> 00:11:30,064
[RICHEH] I don't know.

206
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,732
But if she wanders off
on her own, she'll get lost.

207
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:34,777
[TETIA] We have
to catch up with her!

208
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:45,371
[running footsteps]

209
00:11:45,372 --> 00:11:47,206
[grunts] Hey!

210
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:48,499
[Coco panting]

211
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,000
[TETIA] Agott! [panting]

212
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:53,087
[AGOTT] Tetia,
what's going on? Hm?

213
00:11:54,172 --> 00:11:56,089
[TETIA] Just come with us!
Hurry!

214
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,633
[AGOTT] What? Hold on!

215
00:11:57,634 --> 00:12:00,178
[grunts] What is this about?

216
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,721
[Coco panting]

217
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:07,810
[♪ intense music playing]

218
00:12:23,784 --> 00:12:25,036
[Coco gasps]

219
00:12:26,745 --> 00:12:28,664
[Coco panting]

220
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:30,500
[AGOTT] Coco, stop running!

221
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:35,922
[TETIA] Wait for us, Coco!

222
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:42,596
[brushbuddy squeaks softly]

223
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:48,141
[brushbuddy squeaks]

224
00:12:48,142 --> 00:12:49,436
♪

225
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:53,146
Explain yourself, now!

226
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:54,565
Where are you going, anyway?

227
00:12:54,566 --> 00:12:56,275
There was a witch
outside the shop!

228
00:12:56,276 --> 00:12:58,652
The same one who gave me
the forbidden magic book!

229
00:12:58,653 --> 00:13:00,530
See for yourself, they're...

230
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:03,574
They're, um...

231
00:13:03,575 --> 00:13:05,451
What a waste of precious energy.

232
00:13:05,452 --> 00:13:08,245
Oh, well, at least we're
all together again, right?

233
00:13:08,246 --> 00:13:10,080
Now! Back to the shop!

234
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,499
[RICHEH] That's odd.

235
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,126
We only went
one alley down, right?

236
00:13:14,127 --> 00:13:15,793
But it's so different.

237
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:17,714
And the brushbuddy's gone.

238
00:13:18,423 --> 00:13:20,173
Huh... Good point.

239
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:22,843
These surroundings
are nothing like before.

240
00:13:26,973 --> 00:13:29,266
The walls and floors
are made of a white stone

241
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:30,977
you don't see in Kalhn.

242
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:35,732
Which means,
that this isn't Kalhn.

243
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:38,776
[TETIA] But how can that be?

244
00:13:38,777 --> 00:13:40,694
We didn't pass through
a Windowway,

245
00:13:40,695 --> 00:13:42,780
and it's not like
we could just teleport!

246
00:13:42,781 --> 00:13:45,742
Wait here.
I'll take a look from above!

247
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:48,910
[AGOTT] Tetia may have stumbled
on the right answer.

248
00:13:48,911 --> 00:13:49,912
[BOTH] Huh?

249
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:53,039
We could, in fact,
have been directly teleported

250
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,458
without being aware of it.

251
00:13:54,459 --> 00:13:55,627
[Coco gasps]

252
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:58,836
[COCO] No. Spells like that
aren't allowed, are they?

253
00:13:58,837 --> 00:14:00,423
That kind of magic is...

254
00:14:00,715 --> 00:14:01,757
Forbidden.

255
00:14:01,758 --> 00:14:03,133
[Tetia screams]

256
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:04,968
Oh, no! Oh, no! Oh, no! Oh, no!

257
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:08,430
This is definitely not Kalhn!
We need to get out of here!

258
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:11,057
[AGOTT] Wait. Come back!
What's the matter with you?

259
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:14,561
Tetia, calm down!
Just tell us what you saw!

260
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:18,065
Don't worry about what I saw,
worry about what saw me!

261
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:22,235
[WITCH] I have no business
with the others,

262
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,362
but, oh, well...

263
00:14:23,363 --> 00:14:25,113
[all gasp]

264
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:28,827
[footsteps thudding]

265
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:35,667
[dragon growls]

266
00:14:36,668 --> 00:14:41,755
[WITCH] Coco, I bid you welcome
to the world of magic.

267
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:43,717
[dragon roars]

268
00:14:44,634 --> 00:14:49,096
[WITCH] You are our
one and only hope.

269
00:14:49,472 --> 00:14:50,848
[birds chirping]

270
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:54,351
[QIFREY] Mr. Nolnoa,
have you seen my apprentices?

271
00:14:54,352 --> 00:14:56,019
Not in a while.

272
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,230
Perhaps they got bored
and went for a walk.

273
00:14:58,231 --> 00:14:59,815
What? That's impossible!

274
00:14:59,816 --> 00:15:01,650
How could anyone
get bored in your shop?

275
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:03,777
Why, I could browse this place
all day!

276
00:15:03,778 --> 00:15:05,945
Flattery will get you
nowhere, son.

277
00:15:05,946 --> 00:15:07,531
Something's wrong.

278
00:15:07,532 --> 00:15:09,324
My students
aren't the sort of girls

279
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,535
who would have run off
without thanking you.

280
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:13,579
- But where could they be?
- [footsteps]

281
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:15,248
[TARTAH] I can tell you.

282
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:17,332
I saw them chasing after

283
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:19,418
a strangely dressed witch
a while ago.

284
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:22,880
A witch wearing a mask
that looked like an eyeball.

285
00:15:22,881 --> 00:15:24,006
[wind blowing]

286
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:27,885
[low growl]

287
00:15:27,886 --> 00:15:29,512
[Tetia whimpers]

288
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:35,475
[Coco gasps softly]

289
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:36,811
[AGOTT] Careful now.

290
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:40,939
Maintain eye contact,
and start backing up slowly.

291
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:42,733
Once we're far enough,

292
00:15:42,734 --> 00:15:45,236
I'll give the word and we'll run
with all our might.

293
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:47,238
[Coco gasps]

294
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:52,535
[dragon growling]

295
00:15:56,581 --> 00:15:58,040
[AGOTT] Slowly...

296
00:15:58,917 --> 00:16:00,459
slowly.

297
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,545
[dragon growling]

298
00:16:06,716 --> 00:16:08,008
[AGOTT] Now!

299
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:13,640
[dragon roars]

300
00:16:18,603 --> 00:16:20,647
[dragon groans]

301
00:16:23,733 --> 00:16:25,652
This is it! Let's move!

302
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,365
[all panting]

303
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:35,034
Agott, that was absolutely
incredible!

304
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:36,329
Was it a fire spell?

305
00:16:36,496 --> 00:16:39,414
It used the Fire Sigil
and the Sign of Spiraling Wind.

306
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,291
And you drew it that fast
just now?

307
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:42,460
Of course not!

308
00:16:42,961 --> 00:16:45,963
You prepare mostly drawn spells
in your Palm Quire.

309
00:16:45,964 --> 00:16:47,380
That way, all you have to do
is close the ring

310
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:48,966
and you can use them
in a moment!

311
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:50,592
[Coco squeals] You're amazing!

312
00:16:50,593 --> 00:16:52,218
Will you show me
how to draw that later?

313
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:54,555
Do you even understand
how much danger we're in?

314
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:56,556
[TETIA] Agott!

315
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,935
It's a dead end!
We can't go any farther!

316
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:00,894
Should we try another path?

317
00:17:00,895 --> 00:17:02,897
- [thudding]
- [all gasp]

318
00:17:06,066 --> 00:17:07,651
[TETIA] What do we do?

319
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:09,736
The dragon's going to find us,

320
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:11,488
and gobble us up.

321
00:17:11,489 --> 00:17:12,824
[dragon growls]

322
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:16,076
I don't want to die here.

323
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:21,080
I haven't left a single spell
for the world to remember me by!

324
00:17:21,081 --> 00:17:23,249
Why did I have to
get dragged in...

325
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,460
[Coco gasps]

326
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:28,381
[Tetia gasps]

327
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:34,553
[AGOTT] Tetia, calm down.

328
00:17:34,554 --> 00:17:36,597
We're witch apprentices, remember?

329
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:39,140
Our magic will save us.

330
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:40,518
[Tetia breathes shakily]

331
00:17:43,897 --> 00:17:45,397
I'll use a Wall Breaker spell

332
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:47,106
to create an escape hatch
for us.

333
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:49,484
Richeh, Tetia, buy some time.

334
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:50,861
- [TETIA] Right.
- [RICHEH] Understood.

335
00:17:50,862 --> 00:17:52,278
[TETIA] There.

336
00:17:52,279 --> 00:17:53,655
[AGOTT] Where should I draw it?

337
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:55,240
[RICHEH] Around here, maybe.

338
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:57,283
[TETIA] Add the signs
to this sigil.

339
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,869
Agott, come take a look!

340
00:17:58,870 --> 00:18:00,662
[COCO] She didn't say it,

341
00:18:00,663 --> 00:18:04,041
but I saw in her eyes
that she blames me for this.

342
00:18:04,042 --> 00:18:07,002
[AGOTT] You're right.
This should do the trick nicely.

343
00:18:07,003 --> 00:18:09,797
[COCO] And she's right,
it's all my fault.

344
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,681
Come on.

345
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:22,852
Fly away!

346
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:25,897
[dragon growling]

347
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:34,111
That should keep it busy
for a little while.

348
00:18:34,112 --> 00:18:35,614
Well done, really.

349
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:36,866
[RICHEH] Nice work.

350
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:39,535
Amazing. All of them.

351
00:18:42,329 --> 00:18:43,623
[Coco gasps]

352
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,210
[gasps] Is that...

353
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:52,172
Agott, look up there!
There's a...

354
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:56,802
- [Agott grunting]
- [COCO] Oh, no!

355
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:58,428
What were you thinking?

356
00:18:58,429 --> 00:19:00,137
Never touch a witch
while she's drawing!

357
00:19:00,138 --> 00:19:02,099
I'm sorry! I didn't mean to...

358
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:05,393
Oh, well, that's good to hear!
You didn't mean to.

359
00:19:05,394 --> 00:19:07,646
You didn't mean
to turn your mother to stone!

360
00:19:07,647 --> 00:19:10,315
And you didn't mean
to put us all in danger.

361
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:12,609
It's one accident
after another, isn't it?

362
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:14,903
But that doesn't mean
it's not your fault!

363
00:19:14,904 --> 00:19:16,488
At least get it
through your head

364
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:17,739
how ignorant you are,

365
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:19,450
and stop trying to do anything!

366
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:25,414
Um... What now?

367
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,249
[AGOTT]
There's no time to start over.

368
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:30,585
We'll just have to go back
and find another way...

369
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:31,629
[RICHEH] Done.

370
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:43,140
Excellent. You saved us, Richeh.

371
00:19:43,141 --> 00:19:46,310
Now let's put this
dead end behind us.

372
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,232
I meant this part of the maze.

373
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,860
However, that doesn't mean

374
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:57,363
other interpretations
are invalid.

375
00:20:00,366 --> 00:20:01,616
[Tetia gasps softly]

376
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:02,869
[AGOTT] Tetia.

377
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,767
[Coco breathes shakily]

378
00:20:27,225 --> 00:20:30,687
[COCO] Master Qifrey, I'm lost.

379
00:20:30,688 --> 00:20:32,522
What should I do?

380
00:20:32,523 --> 00:20:34,274
[wind blowing]

381
00:20:38,571 --> 00:20:39,988
[NOLNOA] Qifrey!

382
00:20:39,989 --> 00:20:42,408
Any sign of the girls yet?

383
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:47,496
[QIFREY] No, they're not outside
anywhere nearby.

384
00:20:48,206 --> 00:20:49,622
I didn't expect this.

385
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:51,875
The Brimmed Caps
making direct contact

386
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,292
portends grave danger.

387
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:56,505
[COCO] Hold on! [pants]

388
00:20:58,256 --> 00:21:00,383
That was a Brimmed Cap?

389
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:01,718
My word.

390
00:21:01,719 --> 00:21:03,512
To think one of them
would come here!

391
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:07,432
[QIFREY]
A dangerous faction of witches

392
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:09,809
clad in hats
from a bygone era,

393
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,897
their faces hidden
behind masks.

394
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:16,692
I'd hoped Coco might
eventually lead us to them.

395
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:19,779
I never imagined
they'd come to her.

396
00:21:21,822 --> 00:21:24,741
Tartah, do you remember
anything else?

397
00:21:24,742 --> 00:21:25,952
Please think!

398
00:21:26,869 --> 00:21:28,203
Well, um...

399
00:21:28,204 --> 00:21:30,622
I'm sorry, but not really, no.

400
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:32,289
- It's all right.
- [brushbuddy squeaks]

401
00:21:32,290 --> 00:21:33,417
[QIFREY] Uh?

402
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:35,044
You...

403
00:21:41,092 --> 00:21:43,385
You're the brushbuddy
Coco brought back.

404
00:21:44,262 --> 00:21:46,430
- Were you with them?
- [brushbuddy squeaks]

405
00:21:47,098 --> 00:21:48,432
Where are they?

406
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:53,229
[brushbuddy squeaks]

407
00:21:53,896 --> 00:21:55,439
[indistinct chatter]

408
00:21:56,899 --> 00:21:58,399
[Qifrey panting]

409
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,277
[QIFREY]
It'll be getting dark soon.

410
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:01,862
Please, everyone...

411
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,364
be safe!

